# Agent-Friendly Docs (Agent Score / AFDocs)

This repo is measured against the Agent-Friendly Documentation Spec (AFDocs) and an Ahrefs
orphan-route report. When you create or edit docs, keep these invariants. Breaking one will
regress the Agent Score and likely fail the `afdocs-check` CI.

## llms.txt

- Keep `static/llms.txt` under 50,000 characters. If a section grows, link it out to a
  per-section index (`llms-<product>.txt`) — never inline a monolithic dump.
- It is hand-curated. When you add a new top-level section, add a line to `static/llms.txt`
  AND a matching `customLLMFiles` entry in `src/plugins/llms-html-injector/options.js` (the
  options module that `docusaurus.config.js` requires). Keep them in sync.
- Every link must resolve to a 200 markdown page. Do not link to a page that redirects.

## Markdown parity

- Every doc page must have a working sibling `.md` (handled by the injector). Don't add a page
  type that can't produce one.
- New themed components that render visible chrome (not body content) should be wrapped in
  `data-markdown-ignore` so they're stripped from the generated markdown.

## Routing / orphan routes

- Don't create content-less standalone routes. If you add files that are imported but not meant
  to be pages (fragment trees, helpers), add an `exclude` pattern to the `pages` plugin.
- The classic preset `docs` slot is OFF. New non-product pages go under a product
  `plugin-content-docs` instance or `src/pages/` — not `docs/<name>.md`.
- When you delete or move a page, add a redirect in `vercel.json`. Never leave a dead route.

## URL formatting in chain / reference pages

- On `Public RPC URL`, `Public RPC URL 2`, and `Block Explorer Link` lines, wrap the URL in
  inline-code backticks: `` `https://...` ``. Do NOT use a bare URL, a `[url](url)` self-link,
  or a `<CopyableNoFollow>` wrapper on these lines. (See `editorial-voice.mdc`.)
- Keep trailing guidance prose as plain prose; backtick only the URL token.

## Before you open the PR

- Run `npm run build` then `node scripts/verify-llms-output.js` — it must pass.
- Run `npm run format`.
- If you can, run `npx afdocs check <your-preview-url> --verbose` and confirm no new failures.
